Unpinned test dependencies. (#1458)

* Pinned versions were now so outdated as to be causing issues. No need for them to be pinned at the moment. 
* Additionally, the travis environment comes with outdated versions of pytest and attrs, which leads to errors, so we update those as the first step.

commit.message:
Improved tutorial code a bit. (#1414)

* Improve tutorial code a bit
* Valid HTML 5 - remove unnecessary self-closing tags, fix so `<script>` inside DOM, etc.
* Use `json_script` to securely pass room name
* Disable autocomplete on textarea so chat log not remembered by browser
* Remove unnecessary context argument to `render()`
* Sort some imports
* Upgrade redis version used on Docker
* Note of re_path limitation

commit.message:
Fixed json escaping in the tutorial. (#1398)

mark_safe is not safe in a JS context!

Add support for Django 3.0; drop support for Django < 2.2 (#1389)

* Add support for Django 3.0; drop support for Django < 2.2
* Do not call database operations from async code directly

This prevents `SynchronousOnlyOperation` exceptions that were
introduced in Django 3.0.  See
https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/3.0/releases/3.0/#asgi-support
for further details.
